# Files excluded from the Docker build context.
#
# The build context is what `docker build` sends to the daemon — anything
# listed here is never seen by COPY in the Dockerfile, so it cannot end up
# in any image layer (even one that's later deleted, since deleted files
# still live in lower layers and can be extracted).
#
# Security-critical exclusions go first: secrets, private keys, anything
# that could leak credentials or internal data if the image were exfiltrated.

# --- Secrets and keys (must never enter the image) ---
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
.aws/
.ssh/

# --- Repo metadata and CI ---
.git
.github
.claude
.gitignore
.dockerignore
.editorconfig
.lychee.toml
.yamllint.yml

# --- Python build / cache / dev artefacts ---
__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv
.ruff_cache
pyproject.toml

# --- Internal tooling and audit reports (not for serving) ---
tools/
seo-audits/
*-report.txt
preview-check.txt
normalize-output.txt

# --- Docs and contributor files ---
README.md
LICENSE
CONTRIBUTING*.md
DEVELOPMENT.md
SECURITY.md
RSS_FEED_README.md

# --- Docker-specific files ---
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
nginx.conf

# --- macOS metadata ---
.DS_Store

# --- Large dev-only directories that don't need to be in the image ---
chat-screenshots
email-screenshots
